<!--
  HC career-performance statistic. Drives the per-shift Performance bar in
  the expanded Career Panel and the promote/demote/fire thresholds in EA's
  CareerLevel logic.

  SHAPE: copied verbatim from EA's statistic_Career_Performance_Writer
  --------------------------------------------------------------------
  Extracted from `Data/Simulation/SimulationFullBuild0.package` via
  `Build/_research_tmp/extract-writer-ref.mjs` (gitignored). EA's full
  file is exactly:

      [I c=Statistic i=statistic m=statistics.statistic n=statistic_Career_Performance_Writer s=27784]
        [T n=initial_value]0[/T]
        [T n=max_value_tuning]100[/T]
        [T n=min_value_tuning]-100[/T]
      [/I]

  Three tunables, class=Statistic (NOT Commodity — verified against EA's
  shipped tunings: every adult-career performance stat in the writer-ref
  extract is class=Statistic with this exact 3-field shape).  `initial_value`
  is a deprecated shortcut for `initial_tuning._initial_value` and IS
  accepted by Sims 4 1.124.55's tuning loader.

  WHY NOT EXPLICIT `initial_tuning` TUPLE
  ---------------------------------------
  The structured form `[U n=initial_tuning][T n=_initial_value]0[/T][/U]`
  is also valid but our earlier attempts at that shape failed to register
  with our 31-bit instance ID.  Matching EA's shape exactly removes one
  variable from the debugging space.

  17-BIT INSTANCE ID (s=99701)
  ----------------------------
  EA's career-performance statistics live at s=27784 (Writer), s=27783
  (TechGuru), s=16662 (generic base) — all 16/17-bit.  lot51-core's
  `patches/custom_filter_career_fix.py` shows EA's runtime has a known
  bug that drops 64-bit instance IDs from career-related dicts; the same
  truncation may apply silently to Statistic IDs.  Our 31-bit ID
  (0x3F16A005, from smallInstanceIdFor) was working for every other HC
  tuning but the affordance_injector diagnostic shows HC_Statistic_*
  NEVER appearing in Types.STATISTIC.  Force a 17-bit ID in the EA range
  to remove that variable too.

  Specifically: 99701 = 0x18575, comfortably above EA's used range
  (16662..27784 for performance stats; ~70000 max for any EA stat per
  the SMALL_ID hints in pie-menu-category-id.mjs) and 17-bit clean.

  RANGE -100..+100
  ----------------
  Matches every EA career performance stat.  Critical for our CareerLevel
  scoring tunables (promote=100, demote=-80, fired=-95, warning=-50,
  base_performance=8 per shift, +5 per goal, -35 missed work) to land at
  sensible values rather than saturating immediately as the 0..5 range
  did before commit aabcb30.
-->
<I c="Statistic" i="statistic" m="statistics.statistic" n="HC_Statistic_HistorianLevel" s="99701">
  <T n="initial_value">0</T>
  <T n="max_value_tuning">100</T>
  <T n="min_value_tuning">-100</T>
</I>
